title: Blake Shelton - All 4 Albums
description:
Blake Shelton is the self-titled debut album of American country music artist Blake Shelton. Released in 2001, it features his debut single "Austin", which spent five weeks at the top of the Billboard Hot Country Singles & Tracks (now Hot Country Songs) charts that year. The tracks "All Over Me" and "Ol&#039; Red" were also released as singles, and were both Top 20 hits on the same chart.

   2. "All Over Me" (Earl Thomas Conley, Shelton, Mike Pyle) - 3:14
   3. "She Doesn&#039;t Know She&#039;s Got It" (John Rich, Chris Waters, Tom Shapiro) - 3:18
   4. "Austin" (Kirsti Manna, David Kent) - 3:50
   5. "Ol&#039; Red" (James "Bo" Bohan, Don Goodman, Mark Sherrill) - 3:42
   6. "I Thought There Was Time" (Bobby Braddock) - 3:24
   7. "Same Old Song" (B. Braddock) - 3:50
   8. "That&#039;s What I Call Home" (Richard Mainegra, Shelton, Michael Kosser) - 3:17
   9. "Problems at Home" (Don Ellis, Billy Montana, Shelton) - 4:00
  10. "If I Was Your Man" (Lauren Braddock, Don Henry) - 3:39

The Dreamer is the title of the second album released by American country music artist Blake Shelton. Released in 2003 on Warner Bros. Records Nashville, it features the Number One single "The Baby", as well as the singles "Heavy Liftin&#039;" and "Playboys of the Southwestern World".

Blake Shelton&#039;s Barn & Grill is the third studio album by American country music artist Blake Shelton. Released in 2004 on Warner Bros. Records Nashville, it features the singles "When Somebody Knows You That Well", "Some Beach", "Goodbye Time" (a cover of a Conway Twitty song) and "Nobody But Me".
